  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      There is evidence that inflammatory processes may play a key role during surgical myocardial
      reperfusion. The hypothesis of this study is that colchicine, an anti-inflammatory agent, may
      lead to reduction in periprocedural infarct size, when administered during elective coronary
      artery bypass graft surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
